                                           javafx.scene.control.SelectionMode mode)
        Sets values for partTable. Multiple selection mode added to allow multiple associated parts to be added at once. Brings values from allParts and not partTable from Main form, although the values will be the same. RUNTIME ERROR: Originally, I named this table addProductAllPartsTable but changed the name to partTable, since the values would be consistent with partTable in the Main form, but I forgot to update the name in this method.
        Parameters:
        partTable - Part table being displayed in Add Product form
        partNameCol - Part Name Column in Part table being displayed in Add Product form

        partInvLevelCol - Inventory Level Column in Part table being displayed in Add Product form
        partPriceCol - Price/ Cost per Unit Column in Part table being displayed in Add Product form
        mode - Selection Mode for Part table being displayed in Add Product form

      • searchPartValue

        public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Part> searchPartValue​(java.lang.String search)
        Populates Parts table in Add Product form with parts that have part names that match the value entered into search bar in Add Product form. If no matches are found, allParts is displayed.
        Parameters:
        search - Value entered into search bar in Add Product form
        Returns:
        Parts with matching part names to entered value, or all parts if no matches are found

      • partMatchSearch

        public static boolean partMatchSearch​(java.lang.String search)

        Parameters:

      • productSave

        public void productSave​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        Creates unique product ID, takes values entered into text fields in Add Product form, checks for appropriate values, and uses those values to create a new product which is entered into allParts. See further comments in method for greater detail. Note that productSave will not provide details about exceptions thrown because each check failed provides them.
        Parameters:
        event - addProductSave is triggered (See addProductSave)
